meaning_str.bing:
v. 失败；不及格；倒闭；破产
n. （考试）不及格
网络. 衰退；不合格；不能

失败；未能做到；不足；不及格；倒闭；使失望；出故障；衰退；未做；评定不及格；未履行（某事）
失败；考试不及格；失误；缺点；疏忽；不足之处；失灵；故障

1.en: And if you've done everything In your power , and still "fail" -- The truth of the matter is That you haven't failed at all.
1.cn: 而且如果你已经做每件事物在你的支配下，和静止的“不及格”--物质的事实是你一点也还没有失败。

2.en: He said that under normal circumstances he would be willing to see struggling companies fail.
2.cn: 他说，在正常情况下，他会愿意看到陷入困境的公司垮掉。

3.en: When the assertions fail, it becomes very important to provide error messages that are easy to understand.
3.cn: 当断言失败时，非常有必要提供易于理解的错误消息。

0.en: I don't know. Maybe you wanted your marriage to fail.
0.cn: 我不知道，或许你想让婚姻失败。

1.en: But it matters not. Oakenshield's quest will fail.
1.cn: 但无所谓橡，木盾的远征注定要失败。

2.en: The invasion will fail no matter how many bodies you throw at it.
2.cn: 我们注定失败，无论你让多少战士去送死。

3.en: If you're really one of us, it won't matter to you that you might fail.
3.cn: 如果你真是无畏派的人，就会无视失败的可能。

4.en: We did not fail. And we are not running away. We're just very sensibly regrouping.
4.cn: 我们没有失败，我们现在不是逃跑，我们只是在理智地重组。

5.en: I realized that if I fail to do that, I will be a failure. I struggle with this now.
5.cn: 如果我做不到这一点我将是一个失败。这就是我现在的挣扎。

6.en: If you do, my program will fail. This could be a real weapon. It's worth risking my life.
6.cn: 如果你动手，我的程序就会失败，这是真正的武器，值得我拿生命冒险。

7.en: The throne is mine and I will ascend to it. There is nothing I desire more than this. But you fear I will fail.
7.cn: 皇位是我的，我会顺利继承。这是我最希望看到的。但是您怕我会失败。

8.en: Lady Grantham is not as young as she was, and, as Mrs Crawley says, I'm afraid she'd be almost willing the new regime to fail. Probably.
8.cn: 老夫人没以前那么年轻了，正如卡劳利太太所说，恐怕她更乐意看到新系统失败。很有可能。

9.en: Our priority must be to stop the gate from opening. Fail there, and it's just a matter of time before they beat us with sheer numbers.
9.cn: 我们必须优先阻止传送门打开，如果那里失败，在他们以绝对数量击败我们之前只是一个时间问题了。

10.en: If America Works succeeds, we will reinvent the American dream. If we fail in our attempt, we will admit it frankly and try another.
10.cn: 如果美国就业法案成功了，我们将彻底改造美国梦，如果我们的尝试失败，我们会坦白承认，然后重新来过。

11.en: So you didn't like him. I loved him. Then why don't you teach like him? Because I would never try and be like him. I could only fail.
11.cn: 所以你不喜欢他。我太爱他了。那为什么不像他一样教书呢？因为我永远都无法做到他那个水平。我一定会失败的。

13.en: Then you won't fail and then neither will I.
13.cn: 那你就不会不及格了。那我也不会被莱丽抛弃了。

14.en: I just don't want to fail, Mr. Matthews. Thank you.
14.cn: 我只是不想不及格，麦修斯老师，谢谢。

15.en: And what if you fail to try, Peter? What are you then?
15.cn: 如果你不努力呢，彼得？那又会怎样？

16.en: Oh, I knew you couldn't. What? You set me up to fail? Why?
16.cn: 我就知道你不行。啥？你故意的吗？为什么？

17.en: When the majority of the adjustable rates kick in, in '07, they will begin to fail. And if they fail above 15%, the whole bond is worthless.
17.cn: 等大多数浮动利率在07年开始执行时他们就会开始下跌，如果下跌超过15%，整个债券就一文不值了。

18.en: What you fail to realize is Kripke suffers from a fatal flaw.
18.cn: 你没发觉的是克里帕奇有一个致命伤。

19.en: The point is my natural charisma has made him fail his midterm.
19.cn: 重点是我的自然魅力让他期中考试不及格。
